<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-07T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="1155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1155">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/911.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-07T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1912—12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following to Consul Dye, at Douglas, to-day: [Quotes Department’s
                            telegram of September 7, 1912, 12 noon.]</p>
                        <p>The arms and ammunition are being forwarded to the consul for the use of
                            seriously endangered Americans for the protection of their lives and
                            property. Immediately make all necessary arrangements with the Mexican
                            Government for the entry of these arms and ammunition, so that there
                            will be no delay upon arrival.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>